        <h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>
<p>Complete API documentation for GO-AdminPanel - Restaurant Management System</p>
<aside>
    <strong>Base URL</strong>: <code>https://api.hopa.delivery</code>
</aside>
<pre><code>Welcome to the GO-AdminPanel API documentation. This API provides comprehensive endpoints for managing restaurants, orders, customers, delivery personnel, and more.

&lt;aside&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Base URL&lt;/b&gt;: &lt;code&gt;/api/v1&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Required Headers&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;br&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;Accept: application/json&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;zoneId: {zone_id}&lt;/code&gt; (required for public endpoints)&lt;br&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;Authorization: Bearer {token}&lt;/code&gt; (for authenticated endpoints)
&lt;/aside&gt;

&lt;aside&gt;As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile).
You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).&lt;/aside&gt;</code></pre>

        <h1 id="authenticating-requests">Authenticating requests</h1>
<p>To authenticate requests, include an <strong><code>Authorization</code></strong> header with the value <strong><code>"Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}"</code></strong>.</p>
<p>All authenticated endpoints are marked with a <code>requires authentication</code> badge in the documentation below.</p>
<pre><code>This API uses Laravel Passport for authentication. You can obtain a token by:

&lt;b&gt;For Customers:&lt;/b&gt; POST to &lt;code&gt;/api/v1/customer/auth/login&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;b&gt;For Vendors:&lt;/b&gt; POST to &lt;code&gt;/api/v1/vendor/auth/login&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;b&gt;For Delivery Personnel:&lt;/b&gt; POST to &lt;code&gt;/api/v1/auth/delivery-man/login&lt;/code&gt;

Include the token in the Authorization header as: &lt;code&gt;Bearer YOUR_TOKEN&lt;/code&gt;</code></pre>

        <h1 id="authentication">Authentication</h1>

    

                                <h2 id="authentication-POSTapi-v1-auth-login">Customer Login</h2>

<p>
</p>

<p>Authenticate a customer using various login methods (manual, OTP, or social).
Returns a JWT token upon successful authentication.</p>

<span id="example-requests-POSTapi-v1-auth-login">
<blockquote>Example request:</blockquote>


<div class="bash-example">
    <pre><code class="language-bash">curl --request POST \
    "https://api.hopa.delivery/api/v1/auth/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"login_type\": \"manual\",
    \"email_or_phone\": \"user@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"password123\",
    \"field_type\": \"email\",
    \"phone\": \"+972501234567\",
    \"otp\": \"123456\",
    \"guest_id\": \"guest_12345\"
}"
</code></pre></div>


<div class="javascript-example">
    <pre><code class="language-javascript">const url = new URL(
    "https://api.hopa.delivery/api/v1/auth/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "login_type": "manual",
    "email_or_phone": "user@example.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "field_type": "email",
    "phone": "+972501234567",
    "otp": "123456",
    "guest_id": "guest_12345"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response =&gt; response.json());</code></pre></div>

